data.content:
## What Changed

.NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded from **Microsoft.OpenApi v1.x to v2.x**, which has major breaking changes:

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2) |
|---|---|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any.*` types (`OpenApiString`, etc.) | Removed — use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode` |
| `schema.Nullable` | Removed — use JSON Schema `type` keyword array |
| `OpenApiSecurityScheme.Reference` | Removed — use inline `SchemeId` string references |
| `OpenApiSecurityRequirement[scheme] = scopes` | Now uses `Requirements` list of `SecurityKeyValue` |
| `ReferenceType.SecurityScheme` | Enum removed; references are handled differently |

## Fixed Code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        // OpenApiString replaced by JsonNode
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new Dictionary<string, OpenApiResponse>();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    // Security requirements use SchemeId + list model now
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new()
        {
            SchemeId = "oauth2",
            Scopes = scopes // List<string>
        }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
            {
                // Instead of Nullable = false, ensure "null" is NOT in the type set
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

## Summary of Fixes

1. **`OpenApiString` → `JsonValue.Create(...)`** — all `IOpenApiAny` primitives are now `JsonNode`
2. **`Nullable = false` → remove `Null` from `schema.Type`** — nullable is expressed via `JsonSchemaType.Null` flag
3. **Security scheme references** — no more `OpenApiReference`; use `SchemeId` string directly on `OpenApiSecurityRequirement`
4. **Remove** `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;` — namespace no longer exists; add `using System.Text.Json.Nodes;`
